bug.short_desc: Virtual: Create an architecture for HTML base cell renderer

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 444 Sequence diagram
Sequence diagram

The "getCellProperties" methods return a map with: - classes (string of space separated class names) - style (string of CSS styles) - attributes (string of the cell's attributes) - content (HTML fragment of the cell's innerHTML)
The "states" parameter in the CellRenderer's "getCellProperties" method is a map with the cell's states (e.g. selected, focused, ...).
"getCellProperties" has to return the cell's insets (padding+border) as array
Moving all virtual widget bugs/tasks to Chris.
Move open issues to RESOLVED – LATER, whose last comment is older than a year.
